DataElement.preferredName: Trail Making Test Normative Data Score
DataElement.preferredDefinition: The numerical response that indicates the normalized score of an individual completing the Trail Making Test.  The normative score is the calculated result of the mean time for completion of the test (seconds) minus the time for completion (seconds) divided by the standard deviation.

DataElementConcept.preferredDefinition: A neuropsychological test of visual attention and task switching that requires a subject to connect a sequence of 25 consecutive targets.
